<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-08-21T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-08-21T13:00:00-05:00" n="517" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d517">
                                <note rend="inline" type="source">765.84/899: Telegram</note>
                                <head>
                                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the United Kingdom</hi>
                                        (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Atherton</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    </hi>
                                </head>
                                <opener>
                                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                                        <placeName>
                                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-08-21T19:00:00+01:00">August 21, 1935—7 p.m.</date>
                                        <lb/> [Received August 21—1:15 p.m.]</dateline>
                                </opener>
                                <p>388. Cabinet members have been in consultation today with the
                                    leaders of the Opposition, the Dominion representatives and
                                    representatives of the Committee on Imperial Defence. In the
                                    given circumstances importance is attached here to Mr.
                                        MacDonald’s<note n="62" xml:id="d517fn62">J. Ramsay
                                        MacDonald, British Prime Minister.</note> statement to the
                                    press just before the Cabinet met this afternoon: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                        <p>“I regard the present situation as the most serious thing
                                            we have had to face since 1914. It is a very grave
                                            situation.”</p>
                                    </quote>
                                </p>
                                <closer>
                                    <signed>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Atherton</hi>
                                    </signed>
                                </closer>
                            </div>
                            </body></text></TEI>